claim.claim-text:
3. A non-transitory computer-readable program storage medium including computer program instructions that cause a device to implement a method of sharing tunes between a plurality of devices connected via a network, the method comprising:
storing, at a server, shared tunes and tune data corresponding to each of the available tunes, the tune data including a title, an artist name and an updating date;
displaying an item list of the shared tunes and a device list of other devices determined as being currently connected to the network and eligible for tunes sharing;
transmitting the item list of shared tunes from the server to one of the other devices determined as being currently connected to the network and eligible for tunes sharing;
receiving request for the shared tunes that selects an item from the item list of the shared tunes from the one of the eligible other devices; and
directly providing the shared tunes from the server to the one of the eligible other devices in direct response to receiving the request for the shared tunes from the one of the eligible other devices,
wherein the plurality of devices belong to a predetermined group operably linked to the network.

6. The portable device according to claim 5, wherein
said control unit judges whether a password provided by the one of the eligible other devices is correct;
wherein the communication unit transmits the item list of the shared tunes to the one of the eligible other devices when the password is correct.

8. A portable device for sharing multi-media tunes with other devices connected via a network comprising:
a memory configured to store shared tunes and tune data corresponding to each of the available tunes, the tune data including a title, an artist name and an updating date;
means for displaying an item list of the shared tunes and a device list of the other devices determined as being currently connected to the network and eligible for tunes sharing;
means for transmitting the item list of the shared tunes to one of the eligible other devices;
means for receiving a request for the shared tunes that selects an item from the item list of the shared tunes from the one of the eligible other devices; and
means for directly streaming the shared tunes requested from the one of the eligible other devices to the one of the eligible other devices in direct response to receiving the request for the shared tunes from the one of the eligible other devices,
wherein the portable device and the eligible other devices both belong to a predetermined group operably linked to the network.

12. An eligible device connected to a server, the eligible device comprising:
a storage unit configured to store shared tunes and tune data corresponding to each of the available tunes, the tune data including a title, an artist name and an updating date;
a communication unit configured
to receive an item list of shared tunes from the server;
to transmit a request for the shared tunes that selects an item from the item list to the server, and
to receive the shared tunes streamed directly from the server, the shared tunes streamed directly from the server in direct response to the server receiving the request for the shared tunes; and

a display unit configured to display the item list of the shared tunes and a device list of the server determined as being currently connected to the network and eligible for tunes sharing;
a reproducing control unit, implemented by a central processing unit and configured to control reproducing of the shared tunes while the communication unit is receiving the shared tunes,
wherein the server and the eligible device both belong to a predetermined group operably linked to the network.
